Mick Moloney Irish-American Music and Popular Culture Field Recordings

Purcell, Al (uilleann pipes, whistle, b. May 17, 1929, Dublin, d. Sept 28, 2000, Detroit, MI.) Interview and recording session in Detroit, MI. A student of piper Leo Rowsome, Purcell discusses his personal and musical history, tunes he recorded for Mick Moloney, and Irish music in Detroit. He performs traditional music solo and in duet with his student, Terry McKinney. (Three CDs – Total length: 00:47:22) aiamm32R, 33R
